# EDA and Label Preparation

import random
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import load_img, img_to_array

# Create a DataFrame with file names and labels
train_files = os.listdir(train_dir)
labels = [1 if 'dog' in fname else 0 for fname in train_files]  # 1 = dog, 0 = cat

train_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'filename': train_files,
    'label': labels
})

# Display basic info
print("Number of dog images:", train_df['label'].sum())
print("Number of cat images:", len(train_df) - train_df['label'].sum())
print(train_df.head())

# Plot class distribution
sns.countplot(x='label', data=train_df)
plt.title('Class Distribution (0 = Cat, 1 = Dog)')
plt.show()

# Display a few random sample images
sample_files = random.sample(train_files, 6)
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

for i, file in enumerate(sample_files):
    img_path = os.path.join(train_dir, file)
    img = load_img(img_path, target_size=(128, 128))
    plt.subplot(2, 3, i + 1)
    plt.imshow(img)
    plt.title('Dog' if 'dog' in file else 'Cat')
    plt.axis('off')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Data Preprocessing and Image Generators (Fixed)

# Convert numeric labels to string class names
train_df['label'] = train_df['label'].apply(lambda x: 'dog' if x == 1 else 'cat')

# Split into training and validation sets (80/20)
train_df, val_df = train_test_split(
    train_df,
    test_size=0.2,
    stratify=train_df['label'],
    random_state=SEED
)

print("Training samples:", len(train_df))
print("Validation samples:", len(val_df))

# Image dimensions and batch size
IMG_HEIGHT, IMG_WIDTH = 150, 150
BATCH_SIZE = 32

# ImageDataGenerators
train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rescale=1.0/255.0,
    rotation_range=20,
    width_shift_range=0.2,
    height_shift_range=0.2,
    shear_range=0.2,
    zoom_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip=True,
    fill_mode='nearest'
)

val_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1.0/255.0)

# Flow from directory using DataFrame
train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_dataframe(
    train_df,
    directory=train_dir,
    x_col='filename',
    y_col='label',
    target_size=(IMG_HEIGHT, IMG_WIDTH),
    class_mode='binary',
    batch_size=BATCH_SIZE
)

val_generator = val_datagen.flow_from_dataframe(
    val_df,
    directory=train_dir,
    x_col='filename',
    y_col='label',
    target_size=(IMG_HEIGHT, IMG_WIDTH),
    class_mode='binary',
    batch_size=BATCH_SIZE
)

# Baseline CNN Model

# Build a simple CNN architecture
model_baseline = models.Sequential([
    layers.Input(shape=(150, 150, 3)),
    layers.Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu'),
    layers.MaxPooling2D(2, 2),

    layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'),
    layers.MaxPooling2D(2, 2),

    layers.Conv2D(128, (3, 3), activation='relu'),
    layers.MaxPooling2D(2, 2),

    layers.Flatten(),
    layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dropout(0.5),
    layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
])

# Compile the model
model_baseline.compile(
    loss='binary_crossentropy',
    optimizer=optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
    metrics=['accuracy']
)

# Display summary
model_baseline.summary()

# Train the model
history_baseline = model_baseline.fit(
    train_generator,
    epochs=10,
    validation_data=val_generator,
    verbose=1
)

# ROC and Precision-Recall Evaluation on Validation Data
from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score, roc_curve, precision_recall_curve, average_precision_score, classification_report

# Verify generator mapping
print("Class indices mapping:", val_generator.class_indices)

# Get predictions
val_generator.reset()
y_true = val_generator.classes
y_pred_probs = model_baseline.predict(val_generator, verbose=1)
y_pred = (y_pred_probs > 0.5).astype(int).ravel()

# Derive label names dynamically from generator mapping
target_names = list(val_generator.class_indices.keys())

# ROC Curve
fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_true, y_pred_probs)
roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_true, y_pred_probs)

plt.figure(figsize=(6, 5))
plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f'ROC curve (AUC = {roc_auc:.3f})')
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], linestyle='--', color='gray')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('ROC Curve')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
plt.show()

# Precision-Recall Curve
precision, recall, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_true, y_pred_probs)
ap_score = average_precision_score(y_true, y_pred_probs)

plt.figure(figsize=(6, 5))
plt.plot(recall, precision, label=f'AP = {ap_score:.3f}')
plt.xlabel('Recall')
plt.ylabel('Precision')
plt.title('Precision-Recall Curve')
plt.legend(loc='lower left')
plt.show()

# Classification Report
print("\nClassification Report:")
print(classification_report(y_true, y_pred, target_names=target_names))

# Transfer Learning Model with VGG16
from tensorflow.keras.applications import VGG16
from tensorflow.keras.applications.vgg16 import preprocess_input
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator
from tensorflow.keras import layers, models, optimizers
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, roc_auc_score

# Recreate data generators (disable shuffle for validation)
train_vgg_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    preprocessing_function=preprocess_input,
    rotation_range=20,
    width_shift_range=0.2,
    height_shift_range=0.2,
    zoom_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip=True
)

val_vgg_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(preprocessing_function=preprocess_input)

train_vgg_gen = train_vgg_datagen.flow_from_dataframe(
    train_df,
    directory=train_dir,
    x_col='filename',
    y_col='label',
    target_size=(150, 150),
    class_mode='binary',
    batch_size=32,
    shuffle=True
)

val_vgg_gen = val_vgg_datagen.flow_from_dataframe(
    val_df,
    directory=train_dir,
    x_col='filename',
    y_col='label',
    target_size=(150, 150),
    class_mode='binary',
    batch_size=32,
    shuffle=False
)

# Load VGG16 base (pretrained on ImageNet)
base_model = VGG16(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(150, 150, 3))
base_model.trainable = False  # Freeze convolutional base

# Add custom classifier on top
model_vgg = models.Sequential([
    base_model,
    layers.Flatten(),
    layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dropout(0.5),
    layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
])

# Compile
model_vgg.compile(
    loss='binary_crossentropy',
    optimizer=optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=1e-4),
    metrics=['accuracy']
)

# Train
history_vgg = model_vgg.fit(
    train_vgg_gen,
    epochs=5,
    validation_data=val_vgg_gen,
    verbose=1
)

# Evaluate
val_vgg_gen.reset()
y_true = val_vgg_gen.classes
y_pred_probs = model_vgg.predict(val_vgg_gen, verbose=1)
y_pred = (y_pred_probs > 0.5).astype(int).ravel()

roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_true, y_pred_probs)
print(f"\nROC-AUC: {roc_auc:.3f}\n")

print("Classification Report:")
print(classification_report(y_true, y_pred, target_names=list(val_vgg_gen.class_indices.keys())))

# Save Kaggle Submission File

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import os
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator

# Directories
base_dir = '/Users/daniel/Northwestern Local/MSDS-422/Module 8/dogs-vs-cats-redux-kernels-edition'
test_dir = os.path.join(base_dir, 'test')
submission_path = os.path.join(base_dir, 'sample_submission.csv')

# Load the sample submission to keep the correct ID order
sample_sub = pd.read_csv(submission_path)
print("Sample submission shape:", sample_sub.shape)
print(sample_sub.head())

# Test generator
test_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(preprocessing_function=preprocess_input)
test_generator = test_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    directory=os.path.dirname(test_dir),  # directory containing 'test' folder
    classes=['test'],                     # specify subfolder explicitly
    target_size=(150, 150),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode=None,
    shuffle=False
)

# Predict probabilities 
pred_probs = model_vgg.predict(test_generator, verbose=1)
preds = pred_probs.ravel()

# Match Kaggle format
submission = pd.DataFrame({
    'id': [int(os.path.splitext(os.path.basename(f))[0]) for f in test_generator.filenames],
    'label': preds
}).sort_values(by='id')

# Save CSV
output_csv = os.path.join(base_dir, 'submission_vgg16.csv')
submission.to_csv(output_csv, index=False)

print(f"Submission file saved to: {output_csv}")
print(submission.head())
